<div class="grid-row sidebar-with-body">
  <div class="column-two-thirds">
    <div class="govuk-title length-average">
  <h1>Universal Credit</h1>
</div>
      
<div class="govuk-govspeak direction-ltr rich-govspeak disable-youtube">

  <div role="note" aria-label="Help" class="application-notice help-notice">
    <p>This isn’t GOV.UK - it’s just a prototype. <a href = "https://www.gov.uk" title = "GOV.UK - the best place to find government services and information.">Visit GOV.UK</a>.</p>
  </div>

	
<p>Universal Credit is a monthly payment that replaces some other benefits.</p>

<h2>‘Full service’ and ‘live service’</h2>
	
<p>You’ll get Universal Credit in a different way depending on whether you’re in a ‘full service’ area or a ‘live service’ area.</p>

<p>Which kind of area you live in depends on your postcode.</p>
	
<h2 id='question'>What’s your postcode?</h2>

<p class = "toggle" id = 'full-button' style = 'display:inline-block'
onclick = 
"var x = document.getElementById('full')
var y = document.getElementById('live-button')
var z = document.getElementById('question')
var a = document.getElementById('full-button')
if (x.style.display === 'none') {
    x.style.display = 'block'
    y.style.display = 'none'
    z.style.display = 'none'
    a.innerHTML = 'Choose a different postcode'
    } else {
    x.style.display = 'none'
    y.style.display = 'inline-block'
    z.style.display = 'block'
    a.innerHTML = 'SW1 1AA'
    }">SW1 1AA</p>

<p class = "toggle" id = 'live-button' style = 'display:inline-block'
onclick = 
"var x = document.getElementById('live')
var y = document.getElementById('full-button')
var z = document.getElementById('question')
var a = document.getElementById('live-button')
if (x.style.display === 'none') {
    x.style.display = 'block'
    y.style.display = 'none'
    z.style.display = 'none'
    a.innerHTML = 'Choose a different postcode'
    } else {
    x.style.display = 'none'
    y.style.display = 'inline-block'
    z.style.display = 'block'
    a.innerHTML = 'CC2 3AH'
    }">CC2 3AH</p>

<div id = 'full' style = "display:none">
<h2>You’re in a full service area</h2>
<p>You’ll need to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>set up an online account</li>
  <li>prove your identity online</li>
  <li>report changes through your ‘journal’</li>
</ul>
<h2>How much you’ll get</h2>
<p>The amount of Universal Credit you can get depends on your circumstances, including your income and how many children you have.</p>
<p>Your Universal Credit payment is made up of a basic ‘standard allowance’ and any extra amounts that apply to you.</p>
</div>

<div id = 'live' style = "display:none">
<h2>You’re in a live service area</h2>
<p>You’ll need to claim Universal Credit in person at a Jobcentre.
<h2>Living with your partner</h2>
<p>Your Universal Credit payment is made up of a basic ‘standard allowance’ and any extra amounts that apply to you.</p>
<p>You may get more money on top of your standard allowance if you’re eligible.</p>
</div>	
	
</div>


  </div>
